\f1\b0\fs32 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774 \cf0 \
To finish your programmatic music suite, we need a 
\f2\b \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774 Melody Generator Module
\f1\b0 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774 . This code will generate chord progressions and improvised top-line leads (the solos).\
To keep your tracks cohesive, the melody must change its composition logic to match your 6-hour visual shifts. We do this by setting up a 
\f2\b \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774 Markov Chain Probability Matrix
\f1\b0 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774  [stem-calculative-problem-solving]. This music theory matrix calculates which note is statistically most likely to play next based on the note that just finished playing, ensuring your melodies sound cohesive and intentional.\
\
\pard\pardeftab560\sa80\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs42 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774 \cf0 1. The Multi-Aesthetic Melodic Matrix\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading80\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs32 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774 \cf0 Different visual block styles require distinct musical scales. We define these musical styles as target parameters:\
\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
